# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE waiver list for SANKET images
#
# FORMAT: one CVE ID per line. Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
# POLICY: Only add a CVE here when ALL of the following are true:
#   1. Trivy reports it as CRITICAL.
#   2. The affected package has NO fixed version available upstream ("unfixed").
#   3. The CVE has been reviewed and confirmed not exploitable in this context.
#   4. A comment below documents the rationale and the reviewer.
#
# To find gate-blocking CVEs, run locally:
#   docker build -t sanket/backend:local ./backend
#   trivy image --severity CRITICAL --ignore-unfixed --format table sanket/backend:local
#
# ─── Reviewed Waivers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Add entries in this format:
#   # CVE-YYYY-NNNNN: <package> <affected-version>
#   # Rationale: <why it's not exploitable / no fix available>
#   # Reviewed by: <name/handle> on <date>
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN
#
# No waivers currently active. Run Trivy locally to identify fixable vs.
# unfixable CRITICAL CVEs and update this file with reviewed entries only.
